    "description": "<p><strong>Origins</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Lutum47™ CE originates from the impact site of a meteorite in the Manicouagan</p><p>region of Quebec, Canada, 214 million years ago. Subsequent glacial periods and</p><p>natural erosive processes have refined the igneous rock into a biomineral rich in</p><p>various clays and organic compounds. This biomineral is harvested from</p><p>sediments that have accumulated over millennia in a pristine environment,</p><p>protected under a layer of peat moss which infuses organic compounds into the</p><p>mineral matrix.</p><p><br></p><p>Appearance : powder</p><p>Odor : odorless</p><p>Color : light gray</p><p>pH: not applicable</p><p>Shelf life: 60 months</p><p><br></p><p><u>Formulation Guidelines:</u></p><ul><li>1% - 2%: for a mattifying effect</li><li>3% - 5%: for a sebum regulation, pH regulation of the skin, soft-focus effect</li><li>8% and more: effective hydration, cracked skin treatment.</li><li>10% - 25%: for cleansing products</li><li>35% - 75%: for masks and cataplasms</li></ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><u>Applications</u>: Emollient, Talc &amp; Mica Replacement,</p><p>Cleansing, Hair Structure, Formulation Stability.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><u>Storage and transport conditions: </u>4°C – 30°C, R.H. 30% - 65%</p>",
